The Sabaot community in Bungoma county has welcomed the nomination of Harry Kimutai as Principal Secretary. They said it is historic and a great honour to the marginalised community. There were celebrations in Lolong’bei village near Kaptama market. Excited villagers thronged his rural home in jubilation after the news of is nomination broke out on Tuesday evening. Kimutai was unveiled by President Uhuru Kenyatta as his PS nominee for Livestock. This is the first time since Independence for a member of the minority community to land a PS post. Leaders thanked the President and Deputy President William Ruto.